From: KMA OS <kma@kma-os.dev>
Date: Sun, 21 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0700
Subject: [PATCH] kma: add boot banner + ASCII logo at kernel init

Print the "Welcome to KMA OS" banner and a custom ASCII logo from
init/main.c during start_kernel(), right after set_task_stack_end_magic().
Banner + logo merged into a single pr_info() block (one location only,
avoids the two-patch conflict the old 0002/0003 split had). ASCII-only
so it renders on early-boot and serial consoles without Unicode glyphs.

Built into the kernel image -> persists on every boot, no module to load.
Verify: dmesg | grep "Welcome to KMA OS"

NOTE: hunk targets the call right after set_task_stack_end_magic(). If the
kernel version changes and start_kernel() is reorganised, regenerate from
the new tree (see README "Branding").

Signed-off-by: KMA OS <kma@kma-os.dev>
---
diff --git a/init/main.c b/init/main.c
index 1cb395d..2add6c3 100644
--- a/init/main.c
+++ b/init/main.c
@@ -1011,6 +1011,20 @@ void start_kernel(void)
 	char *after_dashes;
 
 	set_task_stack_end_magic(&init_task);
+
+	/* KMA OS branding banner + ASCII logo (printed early during boot) */
+	pr_info("\n");
+	pr_info("  +======================================+\n");
+	pr_info("  |         Welcome to KMA OS            |\n");
+	pr_info("  |      Minimalist Linux Kernel         |\n");
+	pr_info("  +======================================+\n");
+	pr_info("\n");
+	pr_info("      _  __ __  __    _      ___  ___\n");
+	pr_info("     | |/ /|  \\/  |  / \\    / _ \\/ __|\n");
+	pr_info("     | . \\ | |\\/| | / _ \\  | (_) \\__ \\\n");
+	pr_info("     |_|\\_\\|_|  |_|/_/ \\_\\  \\___/|___/\n");
+	pr_info("     --- Minimalist Linux ---\n");
+	pr_info("\n");
 	smp_setup_processor_id();
 	debug_objects_early_init();
 	init_vmlinux_build_id();
